// @test regression/builtin-shadow-after-use
// @description TV's CE10190 (probed 2026-06-04, INV023): declaring a variable named after a built-in VARIABLE is an ERROR when the built-in was referenced anywhere earlier in source (any scope; global redeclarations too). Without a prior use it stays a warning-only case (CW10011 - hlc3 below gets no error). Both declarations still draw the CW10011 shadow warning on the SemanticAnalyzer channel.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects errors: 1
// @expects error: line=5, message="Cannot shadow the built-in variable 'hl2' because it has already been used as a built-in."
// @expects warning: line=5, message="Shadowing built-in variable 'hl2'"
// @expects warning: line=7, message="Shadowing built-in variable 'hlc3'"
//@version=6
indicator("x")
y = hl2 + 1
if close > open
    hl2 = 1.0
    label.new(bar_index, hl2)
hlc3 = 2.0
plot(y + hlc3)
